    <!-- Main article content -->
    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-green max-w-none dark:prose-invert">

      <h2>Which Service Should You Use?</h2>

      <h3>For Most People: Wise</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Wise (formerly TransferWise)</strong> consistently offers the best exchange rate — typically within 0.5% of the mid-market rate. The fee structure is transparent: a small flat fee plus a percentage. For $500, you'll pay around $5–6 total in fees. Delivery to a Pakistani bank account takes 1–2 business days. Wise is regulated in the US (FinCEN registered) and trusted by millions globally.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Regular remittances of $200–5,000. Users who want the best rate and don't need same-day delivery.</p>

      <h3>For Same-Day Delivery: Remitly</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Remitly</strong> is the market leader for Pakistan remittances in the US. Their "Express" delivery option sends money to mobile wallets (Easypaisa, JazzCash) within minutes. They frequently offer promotional rates for first-time senders. The exchange rate is slightly worse than Wise (by ~0.5–1%), but the speed advantage is clear.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Emergency remittances, first-time senders (promo rates), families on mobile wallets rather than bank accounts.</p>

      <h3>For Large Transfers (Over $5,000): Bank Wire</h3>
      <p>
        For large amounts, a direct <strong>SWIFT bank wire</strong> from your US bank to an HBL, MCB, or UBL account in Pakistan often offers the best total value. The flat fee ($25–45) becomes negligible relative to the better exchange rate at the bank level. Major US banks (Chase, Bank of America, Wells Fargo, Citibank) all offer international wires. Allow 2–5 business days.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Property purchases, large investments, one-time large transfers.</p>

      <h3>For RDA Holders: Roshan Digital Account</h3>
      <p>
        If you have a <a href="/guides/roshan-digital-account-guide-usa/">Roshan Digital Account</a>, wire USD directly into your RDA from your US bank. The RDA converts at near-interbank rates and you can distribute to any Pakistani bank or mobile wallet instantly. This is the most cost-effective method for regular, ongoing transfers — especially if you're also investing in Pakistan through the RDA.
      </p>

      <h2>Tips to Get the Best Rate</h2>

      <ol>
        <li><strong>Check multiple services on the day you send.</strong> Rates change daily. Wise may be best on Monday; Remitly may have a promotion on Thursday.</li>
        <li><strong>Send weekdays.</strong> Weekend transfers often sit in queue until Monday, and you're locked into Friday's rate.</li>
        <li><strong>Avoid airport and hotel exchange counters.</strong> These offer rates 3–7% below the interbank rate — the worst option.</li>
        <li><strong>Use debit card (not credit card) to fund your transfer.</strong> Credit card funding adds 2–4% in cash advance fees.</li>
        <li><strong>Never use unofficial hawala channels.</strong> Hawala is illegal in both the US and Pakistan, uninsured, and untraceable if something goes wrong.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>Is there a limit on sending money to Pakistan from the USA?</h3>
      <p>No legal cap on bank wire amounts. Cash transactions over $10,000 trigger CTR reporting (bank's obligation, not yours). Banks may ask for source of funds documentation for very large transfers ($50,000+). Pakistan permits unlimited inward remittances through official channels.</p>

      <h3>Do I pay US tax on money sent to Pakistan?</h3>
      <p>No. Remittances to family are not taxable US income. Gifts under $17,000/year per recipient need no reporting. Normal family support payments are fully exempt.</p>

      <h3>What is the best mobile wallet to receive money in Pakistan?</h3>
      <p>Easypaisa (Telenor) and JazzCash are the two most widely used mobile wallets. Both accept international transfers from Remitly, WorldRemit, and ACE. Beneficiary needs the mobile app installed and KYC verified (CNIC uploaded).</p>

      <h3>Can I send money to Easypaisa / JazzCash from the USA?</h3>
      <p>Yes — Remitly and ACE Money Transfer both offer direct delivery to Easypaisa and JazzCash accounts in Pakistan. Typically same-day delivery.</p>
    </div>

